sentence.text: The present study, therefore, aimed to evaluate the expression levels of the following growth factors and receptors in squamous cell carcinoma (negative regulation of peptidase activity) of the tongue: the vascular endothelial growth factor (negative regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II)‑C and VEGF‑D, which bind to the cell surface tyrosine kinase receptor VEGF receptor‑3 (VEGFR‑3); C‑C motif chemokine receptor 7 (myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis); neuropilin (positive regulation of neurogenesis)1 and NRP2; and semaphorin 3E (branching involved in blood vessel morphogenesis).
